 ========== ATMOSPHERE =========================================================

  ( US STANDARD ATMOSPHERE PARAMETERIZED BY LINSLEY )
  HEIGHT H IN KM GIVES THICKNESS OF ATMOSPHERE T IN G/CM**2
 H =  -5.8...  4.0 KM ---> T = -1.86556E+02 + 1.2227E+03 * EXP( -H / 9.9419E+00)
 H =   4.0... 10.0 KM ---> T = -9.49190E+01 + 1.1449E+03 * EXP( -H / 8.7815E+00)
 H =  10.0... 40.0 KM ---> T =  6.12890E-01 + 1.3056E+03 * EXP( -H / 6.3614E+00)
 H =  40.0...100.0 KM ---> T =  0.00000E+00 + 5.4018E+02 * EXP( -H / 7.7217E+00)
 H = 100.0...112.8 KM ---> T =  1.12829E-02 - H / 1.0000E+04


